{"id":"mai-hymz","kind":"ticket","type":"task","title":"mai pr full workflow — accept, reject, submit, auto-close, diff, review integration","tags":["pr","workflow","epic"],"body":"## The Dream\n\nmai pr is the git-native PR workflow. No GitHub, no Forgejo, no platform lock-in. Everything stored in refs/notes/maitake, syncs with git push/pull, merges via cat_sort_uniq.\n\n## What exists (shipped in f08c94d)\n- `mai pr 'title' --into main` — creates a PR note (kind: pr) with source/target branches\n- `mai pr` — lists open PRs with ✓ merged detection via is-ancestor\n- PR note has targets: [sourceBranch, targetBranch]\n- Branch auto-detected from HEAD\n\n## What's missing — the FULL workflow\n\n### 1. mai pr show [id]\nShow PR details with:\n- Title, description, status\n- Source → target branches\n- Merge status (merged/open)\n- Diff summary: `git diff \u003ctarget\u003e...\u003csource\u003e` — files changed, insertions, deletions\n- All comments (threaded, with resolved status)\n- Review verdict: accepted/rejected/pending\n- --diff flag: show full diff inline\n\n### 2. mai pr accept [id] [-m message]\n- Adds a comment with resolved=true on the PR note\n- Status stays open (merge hasn't happened yet)\n- Shows: 'PR accepted by \u003cuser\u003e. Ready to merge.'\n- Multiple accepts from different reviewers should all be visible\n\n### 3. mai pr reject [id] -m 'reason'\n- Adds a comment with resolved=false\n- Shows: 'Changes requested by \u003cuser\u003e: reason'\n- PR stays open\n\n### 4. mai pr submit [id]\n- Merges source branch into target: `git merge \u003csource\u003e` (or --rebase)\n- Auto-closes the PR note\n- Shows: 'Merged \u003csource\u003e into \u003ctarget\u003e. PR closed.'\n- If already merged (is-ancestor), just close the note\n- Error if unresolved comments exist (--force to override)\n\n### 5. Auto-close on merge detection\n- When `mai pr` lists PRs and detects ✓ merged, auto-close the note\n- Add a comment: 'Automatically closed: branch merged into target'\n- This means PRs that are merged outside of mai (via git merge, GitHub, etc) still get closed\n\n### 6. mai pr diff [id]\n- Shortcut for showing the diff between source and target\n- `git diff \u003ctarget\u003e...\u003csource\u003e`\n- Supports --stat for summary only\n\n### 7. Review integration\n- The code-review skill (6-pass review) should be able to target a PR\n- `mai pr accept` / `mai pr reject` are the review verdict commands\n- Comments on a PR with file locations: `mai add-note \u003cpr-id\u003e --file src/auth.ts --line 42 -m 'race condition here'`\n- This already works! File-located comments exist. Just needs documentation.\n\n### 8. mai pr comment [id] -m 'message'\n- Alias for `mai add-note \u003cpr-id\u003e -m 'message'`\n- With --file and --line for inline code comments\n- Comments have IDs (already implemented!) so they can be resolved/replied to\n\n## Architecture notes\n- PR is kind:pr — same substrate as tickets, docs, decisions\n- accept/reject are comments with resolved=true/false\n- submit is merge + close event\n- Auto-close is just `mai close \u003cid\u003e -m 'merged'` triggered by is-ancestor\n- Diff uses git plumbing: `git diff \u003ctarget\u003e...\u003csource\u003e` or `git log --oneline \u003ctarget\u003e..\u003csource\u003e`\n- The Engine.IsMerged(from, into) method already exists\n- The Engine.GitBranch() method already exists\n- prBranches(state) helper extracts source/target from targets[]\n\n## Key files\n- cmd/mai/commands.go — runPRCreate, runPRList, prBranches (add runPRShow, runPRAccept, runPRReject, runPRSubmit, runPRDiff)\n- cmd/mai/main.go — pr subcommand dispatch\n- pkg/notes/engine.go — IsMerged, GitBranch\n- pkg/git/git.go — IsAncestor, Diff, MergeBase\n\n## Tests needed\n- Create PR, list, show\n- Accept PR (comment resolved=true visible in show)\n- Reject PR (comment resolved=false visible)\n- Submit PR (merge happens, note closed)\n- Auto-close on merge detection\n- PR on detached HEAD fails\n- PR with same source/target fails\n- Diff output matches git diff\n- Multiple reviewers accept/reject\n\n## Contract\n- Build with: nix-shell -p go --run 'go build -o ~/go/bin/mai ./cmd/mai/'\n- Test with: nix-shell -p go --run 'go test ./... -count=1 -timeout 180s'\n- Do NOT break existing tests\n- Commit each feature separately\n- Push to both: git push origin main \u0026\u0026 git push forgejo main","timestamp":"2026-03-29T12:37:16Z","branch":"main"}

